1
00:00:00,974 --> 00:00:06,513
Namwon town of Honam Province

2
00:00:06,513 --> 00:00:11,985
Was known as Dae-bang
region long ago.

3
00:00:11,985 --> 00:00:17,557
On the east is Chiri Mountain.
On the west is Chuksung River.

4
00:00:17,557 --> 00:00:20,994
Water flowed southwards
with high mountains above.

5
00:00:20,994 --> 00:00:24,987
Full of spiritual energy,
Namwon bred many pretty people.

6
00:00:26,933 --> 00:00:29,703
With endless graves of loyal
officials,

7
00:00:29,703 --> 00:00:32,138
can unswerving loyalty
not exist?

8
00:00:32,138 --> 00:00:35,976
In King Sukjong's early reign,

9
00:00:35,976 --> 00:00:41,214
there lived the only son
of a local governor.

10
00:00:41,214 --> 00:00:44,184
He was 15 years old.

11
00:00:44,184 --> 00:00:47,220
Since he was handsome and righteous,

12
00:00:47,220 --> 00:00:51,625
he was a great man.

13
00:00:51,625 --> 00:00:59,199
On one fine day,

14
00:00:59,199 --> 00:01:02,535
he called his servant Pangja...

15
00:01:02,535 --> 00:01:06,006
Hey Pangja!

16
00:01:06,006 --> 00:01:10,043
Yes master.

17
00:01:10,043 --> 00:01:20,086
I've been here several months,
but I've yet to go sightseeing.

18
00:01:20,086 --> 00:01:21,321
Do you know of any good places?

19
00:01:21,321 --> 00:01:24,658
Why does a diligent student
like you need to know?

20
00:01:24,658 --> 00:01:29,529
You're foolish.

21
00:01:29,529 --> 00:01:31,798
All the greatest scholars
have visited famous sights.

22
00:01:31,798 --> 00:01:36,102
So tell me now.

23
00:01:36,102 --> 00:01:39,105
As you wish Master Lee.

24
00:01:39,105 --> 00:01:40,273
Out the north gate, Kyoryong
Fortress is a good place.

25
00:01:40,273 --> 00:01:44,266
Out the west is Sonwon Temple,
and to the east is Kwan Mausoleum.

26
00:01:43,810 --> 00:01:47,803
To the south is Kwangharu Arbor,
Ojak Bridge and Yongju Pavilion.

27
00:02:07,233 --> 00:02:11,226
They say they're the best places
to visit in the south provinces.

28
00:02:16,242 --> 00:02:30,090
From what you said,
Kwangharu seems the best.

29
00:02:30,090 --> 00:02:34,083
Go get the horse ready.

30
00:02:33,326 --> 00:02:37,319
But your father forbids this,
and we'll get into trouble.

31
00:02:38,398 --> 00:02:40,800
I'll just get permission.

32
00:02:40,800 --> 00:02:42,202
Go mount the saddle!

33
00:02:42,202 --> 00:02:46,372
He mounted the horse,

34
00:02:46,372 --> 00:02:50,365
and Pangja leads the way.

35
00:02:48,575 --> 00:02:51,077
a fan shaped like a
crane's yellow wing,

36
00:02:51,077 --> 00:02:55,682
he flips it open and blocks the sun.

37
00:02:55,682 --> 00:02:59,675
As he travels down the South Road,

38
00:02:59,152 --> 00:03:03,145
the breezy dust from each trot,

39
00:03:04,157 --> 00:03:08,150
flutters in the air

40
00:03:10,864 --> 00:03:14,857
with the scent of peach flowers...

41
00:03:12,899 --> 00:03:16,892
The governor's son is out.

42
00:03:16,803 --> 00:03:20,796
"I traveled from afar
to see Kwangharu's beauty."

43
00:03:21,141 --> 00:03:25,134
Juksung Mountain in the morning

44
00:03:24,277 --> 00:03:28,270
is still covered by late fog.

45
00:03:27,747 --> 00:03:31,740
The river water reflects

46
00:03:33,586 --> 00:03:37,579
green willows and flowering trees.

47
00:03:38,291 --> 00:03:42,284
The spring wind blows gently.

48
00:03:41,728 --> 00:03:45,665
The beautiful columns

49
00:03:45,665 --> 00:03:49,658
soar high into the sky.

50
00:03:49,369 --> 00:03:53,362
The purplish-red tower

51
00:03:52,605 --> 00:03:56,598
embraces the sunlight
and shines radiantly.

52
00:03:55,809 --> 00:03:59,802
In old Wang Bal's poem,

53
00:03:58,711 --> 00:04:02,704
the palace where immortals lived

54
00:04:02,615 --> 00:04:06,608
must be Kwangharu.

55
00:04:05,652 --> 00:04:09,645
Kwangharu is beautiful,

56
00:04:10,290 --> 00:04:14,283
but Ojak Bridge is better.

57
00:04:12,392 --> 00:04:16,385
If it is really Ojak bridge,

58
00:04:13,793 --> 00:04:17,786
then the legend of
Gyunwoo and his love Jiknya

59
00:04:18,198 --> 00:04:22,191
I'll be the Gyunwoo star
on Ojak bridge,

60
00:04:21,668 --> 00:04:25,661
but who shall be my Jiknya?

61
00:04:23,636 --> 00:04:24,804
- Pangja.
- Yes, master.

62
00:04:24,804 --> 00:04:26,639
Today, we'll drink as friends
not as master and servant.

63
00:04:26,639 --> 00:04:41,387
Who is the oldest of you two?

64
00:04:41,387 --> 00:04:45,380
Master, he's a few years older.

65
00:04:52,398 --> 00:04:56,870
Then you have a drink first.

66
00:04:56,870 --> 00:05:01,341
Take this drink.

67
00:05:01,341 --> 00:05:05,334
Today's your day.

68
00:05:04,244 --> 00:05:06,913
such a beautifully written poem.

69
00:05:06,913 --> 00:05:10,906
"I didn't recognize spring's arrival."

70
00:05:10,717 --> 00:05:14,710
"But everywhere, peach
flowers blossomed already."

71
00:05:13,486 --> 00:05:17,479
"A pair of butterflies
left the peach flower,

72
00:05:17,523 --> 00:05:21,516
but they returned missing it."

73
00:05:20,894 --> 00:05:21,995
White and red flowers.

74
00:05:21,995 --> 00:05:22,829
White and red flowers

75
00:05:22,829 --> 00:05:26,232
from the flowery forest,

76
00:05:26,232 --> 00:05:30,036
an angelic girl appears.

77
00:05:30,036 --> 00:05:31,905
Like the sun or moon,

78
00:05:31,905 --> 00:05:36,542
this beautiful girl appears.

79
00:05:36,542 --> 00:05:41,414
She arrives together

80
00:05:41,414 --> 00:05:43,917
with a girl about her age.

81
00:05:43,917 --> 00:05:46,953
The long twisted ropes,

82
00:05:46,953 --> 00:05:49,822
she grabs them

83
00:05:49,822 --> 00:05:58,364
with her delicate hands.

84
00:05:58,364 --> 00:06:04,003
She leans once,

85
00:06:04,003 --> 00:06:07,974
and swings up.

86
00:06:07,974 --> 00:06:21,287
She leans again,

87
00:06:21,287 --> 00:06:31,297
and swings back.

88
00:06:31,297 --> 00:06:32,031
If she flies higher,

89
00:06:32,031 --> 00:06:34,534
she'll meet the Sowangmo angel.

90
00:06:34,534 --> 00:06:37,537
If she flies lower,

91
00:06:37,537 --> 00:06:40,406
she'll meet
the ancient Yoji empress.

92
00:06:40,406 --> 00:06:43,309
She is a girl,

93
00:06:43,309 --> 00:06:47,914
but also an angel.

94
00:06:47,914 --> 00:06:52,585
One moment she's far away,

95
00:06:52,585 --> 00:07:02,462
the next she's very close.

96
00:07:02,462 --> 00:07:07,066
Her swings are in and out

97
00:07:07,066 --> 00:07:11,838
like a swallow's springs

98
00:07:11,838 --> 00:07:16,843
Her lovely motions
put Mongryong in a spell.

99
00:07:16,843 --> 00:07:21,447
Hey, Pangja.

100
00:07:21,447 --> 00:07:25,440
Yes...Yes, master.

101
00:07:26,652 --> 00:07:29,122
Look over there.

102
00:07:29,122 --> 00:07:32,025
Where?

103
00:07:32,025 --> 00:07:42,802
Where my fan is pointed idiot.

104
00:07:42,802 --> 00:07:49,475
Oh, the wrestling match we passed by.

105
00:07:49,475 --> 00:07:51,911
Look carefully.

106
00:07:51,911 --> 00:07:54,881
Can't you see that girl
swinging in the forest?

107
00:07:54,881 --> 00:07:58,751
Looks like a fair maiden
on a swing. Let's go inside...

108
00:07:58,751 --> 00:08:04,557
You think a fair maiden
would be out here on a swing?

109
00:08:04,557 --> 00:08:15,701
You fool.

110
00:08:15,701 --> 00:08:19,694
You should even recognize a
passing dog in your hometown.

111
00:08:21,541 --> 00:08:26,512
Oh, her name's Chunhyang.
She's an old courtesan's daughter.

112
00:08:26,512 --> 00:08:30,505
Looks like her maid
Hyangdan is with her too.

113
00:08:32,618 --> 00:08:38,458
A courtesan's daughter...

114
00:08:38,458 --> 00:08:43,529
This is good.

115
00:08:43,529 --> 00:08:48,935
- Pangja.
- Yes, master.

116
00:08:48,935 --> 00:08:54,907
Go and bring her here.

117
00:08:54,907 --> 00:09:01,514
Please, I can't...

118
00:09:01,514 --> 00:09:06,686
Pangja!

119
00:09:06,686 --> 00:09:12,125
She won't come.

120
00:09:12,125 --> 00:09:16,118
Even though her mother's a courtesan,

121
00:09:17,730 --> 00:09:23,536
Chunhyang is arrogant,
Well read, and writes poems.

122
00:09:23,536 --> 00:09:29,742
She's like a noble's daughter.

123
00:09:29,742 --> 00:09:33,735
She's a courtesan's daughter.
So can't I ask to see her face?

124
00:09:35,148 --> 00:09:40,987
- Bring her to me now.
- Oh master...

125
00:09:40,987 --> 00:09:46,559
Many officials, penniless rakes,
and even nobles of Namwon

126
00:09:46,559 --> 00:09:50,552
tried endlessly to seduce
her, but they all failed.

127
00:09:52,098 --> 00:09:58,137
That's nonsense.

128
00:09:58,137 --> 00:10:02,130
The world's precious beauties,

129
00:10:04,577 --> 00:10:10,683
are destined to have an owner.

130
00:10:10,683 --> 00:10:16,589
So go and get her.

131
00:10:16,589 --> 00:10:20,582
Pangja obeys and runs for Chunhyang.

132
00:10:22,028 --> 00:10:28,601
A fast, chic, and charming Pangja.

133
00:10:28,601 --> 00:10:33,673
Yet a flippant, fluttery,
and sly Pangja.

134
00:10:33,673 --> 00:10:39,545
Like a blue bird delivering
a letter to Sowangmo,

135
00:10:39,545 --> 00:10:45,051
a clever and quite cunning Pangja.

136
00:10:45,051 --> 00:10:50,957
He wears an ox felt hat with silk straps,

137
00:10:50,957 --> 00:10:57,597
a fake jacket and linen pants.

138
00:10:57,597 --> 00:11:03,035
With a stick for a pipe,

139
00:11:03,035 --> 00:11:09,242
and the front end of his
garment tied to his back,

140
00:11:09,242 --> 00:11:15,715
he takes one step,

141
00:11:15,715 --> 00:11:21,687
and takes another.

142
00:11:21,687 --> 00:11:25,680
Step, step, step, step away.

143
00:11:26,826 --> 00:11:32,131
He breaks a branch,

144
00:11:32,131 --> 00:11:37,703
and plays around

145
00:11:37,703 --> 00:11:42,908
with his staff.

146
00:11:42,908 --> 00:11:48,781
He picks up a stone,

147
00:11:48,781 --> 00:11:55,021
and throws it at a willow tree

148
00:11:55,021 --> 00:11:59,014
to scare the birds away.

149
00:12:01,127 --> 00:12:07,133
After his childish play,

150
00:12:07,133 --> 00:12:12,972
he runs to the forest swing

151
00:12:12,972 --> 00:12:17,810
and yells as loud as he can...

152
00:12:17,810 --> 00:12:21,847
...Chunhyang!

153
00:12:21,847 --> 00:12:26,786
Oh gosh! You fool!

154
00:12:26,786 --> 00:12:32,658
My lady almost had
a baby on the swing!

155
00:12:32,658 --> 00:12:38,931
What?!? A baby?

156
00:12:38,931 --> 00:12:44,337
Can you believe it?
A virgin gave birth!

157
00:12:44,337 --> 00:12:46,839
I meant she almost fell,
you idiot.

158
00:12:46,839 --> 00:12:48,741
Chunhyang, there's a big problem.

159
00:12:48,741 --> 00:12:49,675
What is it?

160
00:12:49,675 --> 00:12:50,876
The governor's son came
to visit Kwangharu.

161
00:12:50,876 --> 00:12:53,879
He saw you on the swing,
and wants to meet you.

162
00:12:53,879 --> 00:12:56,315
So let's go.

163
00:12:56,315 --> 00:13:00,308
How come the governor's son
is interested to meet me?

164
00:13:00,219 --> 00:13:05,257
Chunhyang is this...,
Chunhyang is that...

165
00:13:05,257 --> 00:13:08,027
Pangja, you must've
squealed everything about me.

166
00:13:08,027 --> 00:13:12,898
Chunhyang.
If you're a fair lady,

167
00:13:12,898 --> 00:13:15,301
then you should've swung
in your front or backyard.

168
00:13:15,301 --> 00:13:24,810
Tie a rope to your tree,
and make your own swing.

169
00:13:24,810 --> 00:13:26,946
But in this open field,
you flaunt your bare ankles,

170
00:13:26,946 --> 00:13:30,939
tease us with your raised dress,
pretty smile, and giddy laugh,

171
00:13:29,915 --> 00:13:34,153
no wonder he fell for you.

172
00:13:34,153 --> 00:13:39,091
Let's go!

173
00:13:39,091 --> 00:13:44,864
I may be a lowly person,
but I'm not a courtesan.

174
00:13:44,864 --> 00:13:49,034
As a fair lady, you can't
just drag me to any man.

175
00:13:49,034 --> 00:13:55,274
So go alone.

176
00:13:55,274 --> 00:14:05,851
Chunhyang, wait!

177
00:14:05,851 --> 00:14:11,190
Do you want to get into
serious trouble?

178
00:14:11,190 --> 00:14:20,833
The governor will torture you
for being rude to his son.

179
00:14:20,833 --> 00:14:24,826
Is that what you want?

180
00:14:23,402 --> 00:14:25,905
Then tell him this.

181
00:14:25,905 --> 00:14:31,043
"The wild geese desire the sea,

182
00:14:31,043 --> 00:14:33,045
the crabs desire their holes,

183
00:14:33,045 --> 00:14:37,038
and a butterfly desires a flower."

184
00:14:38,083 --> 00:14:42,021
You idiot!
I didn't tell you to chase her away.

185
00:14:42,021 --> 00:14:46,292
I didn't do such a thing.

186
00:14:46,292 --> 00:14:50,930
She cursed me in words
I didn't understand.

187
00:14:50,930 --> 00:15:00,372
And told me
to repeat them to you.

188
00:15:00,372 --> 00:15:06,345
What words?

189
00:15:06,345 --> 00:15:10,349
She said, "the wild geese
desires flowers..."

190
00:15:10,349 --> 00:15:12,218
...or was it the other way.

191
00:15:12,218 --> 00:15:16,822
Really?

192
00:15:16,822 --> 00:15:20,993
They're not insults,
but a proverb with deep meaning.

193
00:15:20,993 --> 00:15:24,897
Like the wild geese desire the sea,

194
00:15:24,897 --> 00:15:28,890
the crabs their holes,
and a butterfly's flower,

195
00:15:29,101 --> 00:15:33,405
she wants me to come
to her.

196
00:15:33,405 --> 00:15:37,176
Let's go.

197
00:15:37,176 --> 00:15:39,845
Now?

198
00:15:39,845 --> 00:15:43,838
My father granted half a day,
so we've got to go back.

199
00:15:46,185 --> 00:15:53,392
Studying in nature
is one of the scholar's ways,

200
00:15:53,392 --> 00:15:58,030
but you're forgetting
to balance your body and mind.

201
00:15:58,030 --> 00:16:02,023
Don't forget to follow the 'six
exercises of a scholar,'

202
00:16:02,001 --> 00:16:06,305
such as archery and horseback riding.

203
00:16:06,305 --> 00:16:10,109
Don't forget to do these things.

204
00:16:10,109 --> 00:16:12,444
If you get sleepy reading
old classics,

205
00:16:12,444 --> 00:16:16,437
read this book to stay awake.

206
00:16:16,282 --> 00:16:20,275
Young Lee sits at his
desk under Chunhyang's spell.

207
00:16:18,517 --> 00:16:20,386
He sees the six officials and
Pangja, and it's Chunhyang.

208
00:16:20,386 --> 00:16:24,379
His mother, and it's Chunhyang.
And his father, it's Chunhyang.

209
00:16:24,390 --> 00:16:28,383
Shapes of the 'Gwon'...
the shape of a sphere, a cube,

210
00:16:28,928 --> 00:16:32,498
Chunhyang's shape,
my shape, the shape of lovers...

211
00:16:32,498 --> 00:16:34,533
they sleep together,
and make a baby's shape.

212
00:16:34,533 --> 00:16:41,307
Master Lee,
what kind of book is that?

213
00:16:41,307 --> 00:16:44,944
- 'The Book of Changes'.
- No, it's the 'Book of Lovers'.

214
00:16:44,944 --> 00:16:49,014
Is there anything about my shape too?

215
00:16:49,014 --> 00:16:54,353
No. There's nothing
about lowly servants.

216
00:16:54,353 --> 00:16:57,923
Bring me the
"Book of 1000 Characters."

217
00:16:57,923 --> 00:17:01,916
Why read a beginner's
book to study for your test?

218
00:17:02,428 --> 00:17:06,421
Because each character
has profound meaning.

219
00:17:05,364 --> 00:17:10,235
The sky was created on the first hour.

220
00:17:10,235 --> 00:17:14,228
Before four seasons existed,

221
00:17:15,140 --> 00:17:19,133
in the empty space lies the 'sky.'

222
00:17:20,012 --> 00:17:24,005
The earth was created
on the second hour.

223
00:17:22,147 --> 00:17:42,167
Since it's composed
of minerals, wood, water, and fire

224
00:17:42,167 --> 00:17:46,160
everything is born and raised
by the 'earth'.

225
00:17:43,435 --> 00:17:47,439
The profound and delicate color

226
00:17:47,439 --> 00:17:51,432
of the North God is 'black'.

227
00:17:51,076 --> 00:17:55,069
The color symbolizing the first
of the five musical scales,

228
00:17:53,545 --> 00:17:55,014
and the center
of four sides is 'yellow'.

229
00:17:55,014 --> 00:17:59,007
We can see thousands of miles away

230
00:17:56,348 --> 00:17:59,551
on the large and high 'pavilion'.

231
00:17:59,551 --> 00:18:03,544
Through the past and the present

232
00:18:02,788 --> 00:18:06,781
is the infinite and endless 'space'.

233
00:18:18,570 --> 00:18:25,044
Go see how far the sun has fallen.

234
00:18:25,044 --> 00:18:31,417
It hasn't set yet, master.

235
00:18:31,417 --> 00:18:41,160
Why is it moving so slowly today?

236
00:18:41,160 --> 00:19:12,825
It seemed to run so fast yesterday,

237
00:19:12,825 --> 00:19:16,818
but today it must have a boil in its foot.

238
00:19:15,527 --> 00:19:19,520
The guard shouts...

239
00:19:18,630 --> 00:19:22,623
Close the gates!

240
00:19:20,332 --> 00:19:24,325
Young Lee is ecstatic and says...

241
00:19:24,436 --> 00:19:28,429
Let's go to Chunhyang's house.

242
00:19:26,538 --> 00:19:30,531
Pangja leads the way.

243
00:19:30,409 --> 00:19:34,402
On the way to Chunhyang's home,

244
00:19:35,481 --> 00:19:39,474
a wide, dusty road leads into a trail,

245
00:19:40,085 --> 00:19:44,078
while the moonlight seeps
through the clouds.

246
00:19:43,889 --> 00:19:47,882
And with the green willows
between the flowering trees,

247
00:19:45,390 --> 00:19:49,383
the night is so lovely.

248
00:19:49,428 --> 00:19:53,421
When they arrive at
Chunhyang's home,

249
00:19:52,664 --> 00:19:56,657
on the left are green pine trees,

250
00:19:58,370 --> 00:20:02,363
on the right are green bamboo trees.

251
00:20:01,673 --> 00:20:05,666
The wavy pine trees stand calm.

252
00:20:03,342 --> 00:20:04,309
What shall we do now, master?

253
00:20:04,309 --> 00:20:08,347
Call her.

254
00:20:08,347 --> 00:20:12,340
Sir, I think it would be better
if you call her yourself.

255
00:20:12,518 --> 00:20:16,511
Just do as I said. Call her now.

256
00:20:16,155 --> 00:20:18,690
Chunhyang! Are you awake?

257
00:20:18,690 --> 00:20:21,393
My master is here
so come out this instant!

258
00:20:21,393 --> 00:20:24,496
Is this some prank?

259
00:20:24,496 --> 00:20:31,570
It's me Pangja.

260
00:20:31,570 --> 00:20:35,674
What are you doing here?

261
00:20:35,674 --> 00:20:40,412
I've brought the governor's son.

262
00:20:40,412 --> 00:20:47,486
What?!?

263
00:20:47,486 --> 00:20:54,226
The governor's son? You fool!

264
00:20:54,226 --> 00:21:00,699
You should've told me
earlier he was coming.

265
00:21:00,699 --> 00:21:03,669
Look at you.

266
00:21:03,669 --> 00:21:07,662
You're better off worrying
about your underpants instead.

267
00:21:07,172 --> 00:21:10,342
Oh gosh!

268
00:21:10,342 --> 00:21:14,335
Hyangdan!
Go open the gate for them.

269
00:21:13,478 --> 00:21:17,471
Master Lee, it's an honor to
have you at our humble home.

270
00:21:17,182 --> 00:21:21,175
Please do come in.

271
00:21:24,656 --> 00:21:27,793
'Lotus Pavilion...'

272
00:21:27,793 --> 00:21:31,786
The writing is refined and graceful.

273
00:21:30,195 --> 00:21:34,199
Who wrote this?

274
00:21:34,199 --> 00:21:38,370
It's a girl's clumsy writing.

275
00:21:38,370 --> 00:21:43,575
Although a lotus blossoms from clay,

276
00:21:43,575 --> 00:21:47,568
it's clean and enchanting,
and its scent travels for miles.

277
00:21:48,580 --> 00:21:52,573
The farther a lotus scent
travels, the fresher and purer.

278
00:21:53,719 --> 00:21:57,712
Your scent fills my room,
and intoxicates me.

279
00:21:56,555 --> 00:22:00,548
Instead of the lotus, you're
the best flower, Chunhyang.

280
00:21:58,891 --> 00:22:02,261
A painting of the famous Minister Kang.

281
00:22:02,261 --> 00:22:10,836
Did you draw this too?

282
00:22:10,836 --> 00:22:13,705
You're making me blush, Master Lee.

283
00:22:13,705 --> 00:22:17,698
While fishing with no bait,
he waits forever to meet King Moon,

284
00:22:16,808 --> 00:22:20,779
and later fulfills his dream.

285
00:22:20,779 --> 00:22:26,051
While avoiding a disrupt world
and becoming a hermit,

286
00:22:26,051 --> 00:22:30,044
it's an ambitious life
that understands patience.

287
00:22:31,623 --> 00:22:35,594
Your wish to meet a good husband

288
00:22:35,594 --> 00:22:39,587
is shown in the painting.

289
00:22:39,064 --> 00:22:43,057
Did you come here thinking
I was an easy courtesan?

290
00:22:45,570 --> 00:22:49,563
You're a talented writer,
and so am I.

291
00:22:48,674 --> 00:22:50,609
Don't you think its fate

292
00:22:50,609 --> 00:22:54,602
that brought us here together?

293
00:22:53,745 --> 00:22:58,884
Hyangdan...

294
00:22:58,884 --> 00:23:02,877
He's fallen for Chunhyang
so you have to serve him well.

295
00:23:00,886 --> 00:23:04,879
If things go well, all of
Namwon might be Chunhyang's.

296
00:23:11,563 --> 00:23:14,066
Wolmae...

297
00:23:14,066 --> 00:23:18,059
Part of the reason why I
brought him here is for me.

298
00:23:17,636 --> 00:23:21,940
So put in a good word for me.

299
00:23:21,940 --> 00:23:26,912
Come on Wolmae.

300
00:23:26,912 --> 00:23:30,905
It's time for me move up,
so I can brag about myself.

301
00:23:28,747 --> 00:23:33,919
You're out of your mind.

302
00:23:33,919 --> 00:23:42,694
- Don't steal my part of the gold.
- Wolmae...

303
00:23:42,694 --> 00:23:49,601
Wolmae?

304
00:23:49,601 --> 00:23:53,594
Just shut up,
and pull out the chicken hairs.

305
00:24:04,483 --> 00:24:20,599
Master Lee, this is my mother.

306
00:24:20,599 --> 00:24:37,049
It's my honor to meet you.

307
00:24:37,049 --> 00:24:44,923
Good evening.

308
00:24:44,923 --> 00:24:48,916
If I knew you were coming,
I would've greeted you formally.

309
00:24:52,964 --> 00:24:56,957
What brings a noble young man
to our house this evening?

310
00:25:01,706 --> 00:25:10,449
Please come in and sit comfortably.

311
00:25:10,449 --> 00:25:14,442
Thank you.

312
00:25:18,590 --> 00:25:27,632
A few days ago,
I saw Chunhyang at Kwangharu,

313
00:25:27,632 --> 00:25:31,625
and I instantly adored her like
a butterfly desiring a flower.

314
00:25:35,540 --> 00:25:39,533
How would you feel if I took
Chunhyang's hand as my wife?

315
00:25:44,716 --> 00:25:48,709
You're the son of a noble,
but Chunhyang is of a low class.

316
00:25:53,792 --> 00:25:57,785
If the butterfly just came to
pick the flower and leave,

317
00:26:02,601 --> 00:26:10,642
our world would be miserable.

318
00:26:10,642 --> 00:26:13,478
So please stay and just
have a drink with us.

319
00:26:13,478 --> 00:26:19,017
I know this is informal,
but I think this is fate also.

320
00:26:19,017 --> 00:26:23,010
I'll be a good husband,
so give me your permission.

321
00:26:27,859 --> 00:26:31,852
When her father was
the governor of Namwon,

322
00:26:36,001 --> 00:26:38,170
he picked me as his
courtesan for one night,

323
00:26:38,170 --> 00:26:46,945
and so she was conceived.

324
00:26:46,945 --> 00:26:49,614
He promised to take us to Seoul,

325
00:26:49,614 --> 00:26:51,683
but he passed away suddenly.

326
00:26:51,683 --> 00:26:58,657
So I raised her all by myself.

327
00:26:58,657 --> 00:27:02,650
And I did it with the utmost care.

328
00:26:59,991 --> 00:27:03,984
Since you're so insistent,
I could give you my approval,

329
00:27:04,829 --> 00:27:06,064
but it's not my decision.

330
00:27:06,064 --> 00:27:10,057
Chunhyang, what do you think?

331
00:27:09,668 --> 00:27:13,661
Since Master Lee is so intent,
does a lowly girl have a choice?

332
00:27:13,171 --> 00:27:16,174
But...

333
00:27:16,174 --> 00:27:18,977
Since the future is unforeseeable,

334
00:27:18,977 --> 00:27:21,613
please vow...

335
00:27:21,613 --> 00:27:25,606
...your eternal love for me.

336
00:27:25,951 --> 00:27:29,944
"Like the sun and the moon,

337
00:27:27,986 --> 00:27:31,979
my love will never change."

338
00:27:30,922 --> 00:27:34,915
...Mongryong Lee

339
00:27:33,024 --> 00:27:35,794
Chunhyang, my child.

340
00:27:35,794 --> 00:27:37,162
Every woman does it.

341
00:27:37,162 --> 00:27:41,155
Don't be scared and do what he says.

342
00:27:39,231 --> 00:27:43,201
Also...

343
00:27:43,201 --> 00:27:45,837
Lay this on the floor.

344
00:27:45,837 --> 00:27:49,941
He has to know you are a virgin.

345
00:27:49,941 --> 00:27:53,934
So don't forget to show
it to him.

346
00:27:57,148 --> 00:28:01,653
Chunhyang, come here.

347
00:28:01,653 --> 00:28:06,691
The night is late.
Let's sleep.

348
00:28:06,691 --> 00:28:13,632
I don't want to.

349
00:28:13,632 --> 00:28:16,935
Listen to me and come here.

350
00:28:16,935 --> 00:28:20,205
They say for a married couple

351
00:28:20,205 --> 00:28:24,109
ever-lasting happiness
depends on the first night.

352
00:28:24,109 --> 00:28:28,102
But if you grab the wife's hand,
they say it's bad luck.

353
00:28:27,646 --> 00:28:31,639
The moon is bright.
Oh yes, it is bright.

354
00:28:32,217 --> 00:28:35,720
The moon is brighter than ever.

355
00:28:35,720 --> 00:29:13,925
My wretched moon is bright.

356
00:29:13,925 --> 00:29:16,127
The reflection from
Chunhyang's room is bright.

357
00:29:16,127 --> 00:29:19,898
When I was young,

358
00:29:19,898 --> 00:29:23,891
I was known as
"Bright Moon" of Namwon,

359
00:29:22,901 --> 00:29:25,837
but I am bright no more

360
00:29:25,837 --> 00:29:29,830
as my face grew old.

361
00:29:30,175 --> 00:29:32,911
As one day, two days,
and several days pass,

362
00:29:32,911 --> 00:29:34,346
the young lovers'
shyness disappears,

363
00:29:34,346 --> 00:29:37,916
and they grow fondly intimate.

364
00:29:37,916 --> 00:29:41,186
One day,
as they hug and roll around,

365
00:29:41,186 --> 00:29:47,225
they enjoy the 'Love Song.'

366
00:29:47,225 --> 00:29:51,218
Come here,
ride my back and we'll play.

367
00:29:49,961 --> 00:29:53,954
Come here,
ride my back and we'll play.

368
00:29:53,798 --> 00:29:57,791
Love, love, love, my love.

369
00:29:58,303 --> 00:30:02,296
What a love, my beloved.

370
00:30:03,241 --> 00:30:07,234
Yes...my love.

371
00:30:12,150 --> 00:30:16,143
Oh...my love.

372
00:30:23,261 --> 00:30:27,254
What would you like to eat?

373
00:30:33,071 --> 00:30:37,064
What would you like to eat?

374
00:30:41,813 --> 00:30:45,806
A poked round watermelon

375
00:30:50,155 --> 00:30:54,148
poured with sweet white honey.

376
00:30:54,859 --> 00:30:58,852
Take the seeds out and taste
a juicy red piece.

377
00:30:59,931 --> 00:31:08,873
Savor it all in one big bite.

378
00:31:08,873 --> 00:31:12,866
No, I don't want any.

379
00:31:14,779 --> 00:31:18,772
Then what would you like to eat?

380
00:31:19,951 --> 00:31:23,944
What would you like to eat?

381
00:31:25,056 --> 00:31:32,897
A short, thick, and oval

382
00:31:32,897 --> 00:31:36,890
sweet cucumber,
eggplant, or melon?

383
00:31:40,939 --> 00:31:44,932
No, I don't want any.

384
00:31:48,279 --> 00:31:52,272
Then what would you like to eat?

385
00:31:55,854 --> 00:31:59,847
What do you like to eat?

386
00:32:24,115 --> 00:32:27,051
Would you like cherries or grapes?

387
00:32:27,051 --> 00:32:31,044
A taffy or tangerine candy my dear?

388
00:32:30,221 --> 00:32:36,060
Then my love...

389
00:32:36,060 --> 00:32:40,053
What would you like to eat?

390
00:32:37,095 --> 00:32:41,088
What do you want to eat?

391
00:32:39,130 --> 00:32:40,498
How did they find out?

392
00:32:40,498 --> 00:32:45,136
Who's the bastard that told them?

393
00:32:45,136 --> 00:32:47,505
When the morning cock cried,

394
00:32:47,505 --> 00:32:51,498
the governor suddenly came and
demanded your whereabouts.

395
00:32:51,309 --> 00:32:55,302
Forgive me, I had no choice.

396
00:32:52,143 --> 00:32:56,136
Since your father knows
already, don't try to lie to him.

397
00:32:58,683 --> 00:33:02,676
Tell him you won't leave anymore
and you'll concentrate on the exam.

398
00:33:01,219 --> 00:33:06,057
Okay?

399
00:33:06,057 --> 00:33:10,050
My love, my treasure, my joy.

400
00:33:14,465 --> 00:33:18,458
Oh yes...you're my beloved.

401
00:33:24,475 --> 00:33:28,468
When you die, become a flower.

402
00:33:26,277 --> 00:33:30,270
A peach flower
that blossoms in the spring.

403
00:33:39,223 --> 00:33:43,216
When I die,
I'll become a tiger butterfly.

404
00:33:41,492 --> 00:33:43,528
On a beautiful spring day,

405
00:33:43,528 --> 00:33:47,521
if I dance around you,

406
00:33:47,432 --> 00:33:51,425
then recognize it is me.

407
00:33:53,571 --> 00:33:57,564
If the flower withers,

408
00:33:55,473 --> 00:33:59,466
the butterflies don't visit anymore.

409
00:33:57,408 --> 00:34:01,401
So I don't want to be a flower.

410
00:34:02,080 --> 00:34:06,073
Then there's another after you die.

411
00:34:05,550 --> 00:34:09,543
You become the Bell of Chongno,

412
00:34:08,519 --> 00:34:12,512
and I'll be the hammer that hits it.

413
00:34:14,125 --> 00:34:18,118
In the night,
I'll hit it 28 times,

414
00:34:18,463 --> 00:34:22,467
In the day,
I'll hit it 33 times.

415
00:34:22,467 --> 00:34:26,460
When I hit you,

416
00:34:25,536 --> 00:34:29,529
recognize it is me.

417
00:34:32,210 --> 00:34:36,203
I don't want to be a bell.

418
00:34:34,412 --> 00:34:38,405
Then there's another after you die.

419
00:34:36,347 --> 00:34:40,340
You'll be the Yin,

420
00:34:41,352 --> 00:34:45,390
such as the 'earth',

421
00:34:45,390 --> 00:34:49,383
'shade,' 'wife',

422
00:34:50,028 --> 00:34:54,021
and 'woman'.

423
00:34:57,602 --> 00:35:01,595
I'll be the Yang,

424
00:35:02,540 --> 00:35:08,279
such as the 'sky',

425
00:35:08,279 --> 00:35:16,287
'sun',

426
00:35:16,287 --> 00:35:20,058
'light',

427
00:35:20,058 --> 00:35:23,661
'husband',

428
00:35:23,661 --> 00:35:27,654
and 'man'.

429
00:35:31,335 --> 00:35:35,328
We will live happily forever

430
00:35:35,206 --> 00:35:39,199
when we become 'one'.

431
00:35:39,043 --> 00:35:46,350
Hey Hyangdan.

432
00:35:46,350 --> 00:35:50,343
Oh my! You're bad.

433
00:36:01,399 --> 00:36:10,675
Master Lee.

434
00:36:10,675 --> 00:36:14,668
Master Lee!

435
00:36:13,611 --> 00:36:17,604
What are you doing here?

436
00:36:18,883 --> 00:36:21,385
Where have you been lately?

437
00:36:21,385 --> 00:36:25,389
Were you too busy to study
and hear the good news?

438
00:36:25,389 --> 00:36:29,727
What sort of news father?

439
00:36:29,727 --> 00:36:34,265
I've been appointed
to the King's cabinet.

440
00:36:34,265 --> 00:36:37,201
I'll finish up here

441
00:36:37,201 --> 00:36:41,194
so take your mother
to Seoul ahead of me.

442
00:36:40,571 --> 00:36:49,247
Master Lee is here.

443
00:36:49,247 --> 00:36:53,240
My son-in-law is home!
But why are you here so early?

444
00:36:53,417 --> 00:36:57,555
Well, I'm glad.

445
00:36:57,555 --> 00:37:01,548
I just sewed an autumn jacket
for you. Come up and try it on.

446
00:37:02,293 --> 00:37:06,286
Why did you walk here without Pangja?

447
00:37:06,264 --> 00:37:10,257
Why do you look so worried?

448
00:37:10,568 --> 00:37:14,438
Did your father scold you?

449
00:37:14,438 --> 00:37:18,431
Please say something.

450
00:37:16,707 --> 00:37:20,700
I don't smell any alcohol.

451
00:37:20,545 --> 00:37:24,538
...no fever.

452
00:37:24,482 --> 00:37:29,353
What's wrong?

453
00:37:29,353 --> 00:37:33,346
My father has been appointed
as a minister in Seoul.

454
00:37:40,531 --> 00:37:46,504
What great news.

455
00:37:46,504 --> 00:37:53,277
That's a high rank in the government.

456
00:37:53,277 --> 00:38:02,286
But why aren't you happy?

457
00:38:02,286 --> 00:38:06,279
I have to leave for Seoul tomorrow.

458
00:38:34,986 --> 00:38:42,793
Are you worried I won't follow you?

459
00:38:42,793 --> 00:38:46,786
A woman follows
her husband wherever he goes.

460
00:38:48,466 --> 00:38:50,801
There's nothing
in Namwon if you're away.

461
00:38:50,801 --> 00:38:54,794
My mother said if people
discover our marriage,

462
00:38:57,375 --> 00:39:01,368
I'll be disowned,
and forbidden to take the state exam.

463
00:38:59,543 --> 00:39:03,536
So she insists I don't mention
our marriage to my father.

464
00:39:03,014 --> 00:39:06,651
Are you saying we must separate?

465
00:39:06,651 --> 00:39:10,554
Only for a little while.

466
00:39:10,554 --> 00:39:14,547
All I can do is come back for you later.

467
00:39:15,626 --> 00:39:19,619
Oh my husband!

468
00:39:22,466 --> 00:39:26,459
Is what you said

469
00:39:25,803 --> 00:39:29,796
a quirk, a joke,

470
00:39:28,739 --> 00:39:32,732
a mistake, or nonsense?

471
00:39:31,442 --> 00:39:35,435
Watching me kill myself...

472
00:39:38,316 --> 00:39:42,309
Is that what you want?

473
00:39:42,853 --> 00:39:46,846
When we met the first time,

474
00:40:09,347 --> 00:40:11,649
what did you say?

475
00:40:11,649 --> 00:40:15,642
We swore to the
mountains and the ocean

476
00:40:12,717 --> 00:40:16,710
with the sun and the moon
as our witnesses...

477
00:40:14,819 --> 00:40:18,812
Until the mulberry field
becomes the sea

478
00:40:19,323 --> 00:40:23,316
or the sea becomes the mulberry field,

479
00:40:20,658 --> 00:40:24,651
we will never part.

480
00:40:22,827 --> 00:40:26,820
Not even a year has past,

481
00:40:23,894 --> 00:40:27,887
and you're saying farewell?

482
00:40:26,063 --> 00:40:30,056
There is the cloud you swore on.

483
00:40:29,133 --> 00:40:33,804
Speak to me.

484
00:40:33,804 --> 00:40:37,797
Speak to me.

485
00:40:39,410 --> 00:40:41,645
You begged me

486
00:40:41,645 --> 00:40:45,638
to be your wife,

487
00:40:45,716 --> 00:40:49,709
but now you ruined my life!

488
00:40:49,954 --> 00:40:53,724
My husband, take this drink.

489
00:40:53,724 --> 00:40:55,626
While you travel to Seoul,

490
00:40:55,626 --> 00:40:59,619
think of my love for you
when you see the blue river.

491
00:40:57,895 --> 00:41:23,187
Our enemy is not a person,

492
00:41:23,187 --> 00:41:27,180
the enemy is the class that divides us.

493
00:41:26,424 --> 00:41:30,417
Chunhyang, take this mirror.

494
00:41:30,861 --> 00:41:35,699
My love is as pure as
the mirror's reflection.

495
00:41:35,699 --> 00:41:39,692
Cherish it and think
of me when you use it.

496
00:41:39,437 --> 00:41:42,173
Take this, my husband.

497
00:41:42,173 --> 00:41:46,166
My unchangeable love is the
same as the color of jade.

498
00:41:44,508 --> 00:41:48,501
Think of me when you see it.

499
00:41:45,776 --> 00:41:48,879
After Namwon,
there's Osu and lmsil,

500
00:41:48,879 --> 00:41:50,781
and then Chunju
which is famous for its fans.

501
00:41:50,781 --> 00:41:51,816
After Yusan, which is known
for its fur and leather,

502
00:41:51,816 --> 00:41:54,185
there's fine honey
and ginseng in Kongju.

503
00:41:54,185 --> 00:41:58,178
Then there's Chunan,
which is famous for its carps.

504
00:41:56,420 --> 00:42:00,413
Then Suwon and Kwachon,
which is 32 km from Seoul.

505
00:41:57,088 --> 00:42:03,060
Bandits in Seoul are so territorial,

506
00:42:03,060 --> 00:42:07,053
country people start to shiver
when they pass Kwachon.

507
00:42:06,931 --> 00:42:15,139
Chunhyang...

508
00:42:15,139 --> 00:42:19,132
When I pass the exam,
I'll send a royal palanquin for you.

509
00:42:27,952 --> 00:42:32,056
So wait until that day.

510
00:42:32,056 --> 00:42:36,049
A royal palanquin is only ridden
by high-ranking officials.

511
00:42:54,745 --> 00:42:58,738
Do you think this day will come
before I become an old hag?

512
00:43:01,552 --> 00:43:05,545
Meanwhile,
his mother prepares to leave.

513
00:43:06,790 --> 00:43:09,527
Double palanquins...

514
00:43:09,527 --> 00:43:11,495
Single palanquins...

515
00:43:11,495 --> 00:43:17,735
Horses and soldiers are busy.

516
00:43:17,735 --> 00:43:20,571
Nervous Pangja
dashes with Mongryong's horse.

517
00:43:20,571 --> 00:43:23,574
Ring...ring...ring...ring...

518
00:43:23,574 --> 00:43:28,045
He arrives at Chunhyang's home.

519
00:43:28,045 --> 00:43:29,880
