After he became the ethics official,

785
00:10:38,684 --> 00:10:44,690
the King secretly makes him

786
00:10:44,690 --> 00:10:48,683
his emissary to inspect Cholla Province

787
00:10:49,695 --> 00:10:56,702
and gives him his assignment,

788
00:10:56,702 --> 00:11:00,695
with a symbolic ruler and royal insignia.

789
00:11:02,708 --> 00:11:06,701
He bids his family farewell
and leaves for Cholla Province.

790
00:11:08,714 --> 00:11:14,720
He leaves the South Gate of Seoul,

791
00:11:14,720 --> 00:11:18,713
and crosses Han River
and several streams.

792
00:11:20,726 --> 00:11:25,731
Then he passes
many small villages like

793
00:11:25,731 --> 00:11:29,724
Mirookdangee,
Kolsagunae, and Ssangyoochon,

794
00:11:31,737 --> 00:11:35,730
and many marketplaces,
like Dukjum and Ohmu

795
00:11:36,742 --> 00:11:40,735
and many towns like Sosa,
Kwangjung, and Morowon,

796
00:11:41,747 --> 00:11:48,754
He finally arrives at

797
00:11:48,754 --> 00:11:52,747
Yusan town.

798
00:11:54,760 --> 00:12:00,766
- First Deputy.
- Yes, sir.

799
00:12:00,766 --> 00:12:06,772
Go to the west provinces.
Start in Yusan and lksan.

800
00:12:06,772 --> 00:12:11,777
Then Kimjae and the rest.

801
00:12:11,777 --> 00:12:16,782
We'll meet at Kwangharu
on the 15th of next month.

802
00:12:16,782 --> 00:12:20,786
Yes, sir.

803
00:12:20,786 --> 00:12:25,791
- Second Deputy.
-Yes, sir.

804
00:12:25,791 --> 00:12:31,797
Go to the east and
check Kosan, Kumsan,

805
00:12:31,797 --> 00:12:37,803
Muju, Yongdam, and the rest.

806
00:12:37,803 --> 00:12:41,796
- Meet on the same day too.
- Yes, sir.

807
00:12:43,809 --> 00:12:47,802
Hey, you dear farmers,
listen to what I say.

808
00:12:45,811 --> 00:12:49,804
Listen to what I say.

809
00:12:46,812 --> 00:12:50,805
Drop by drop,
your sweat turns into fruit.

810
00:12:48,814 --> 00:12:52,807
Chop by chop,
your grain turns into gold.

811
00:12:49,815 --> 00:12:52,818
Come here. Eat with us.

812
00:12:52,818 --> 00:12:55,821
No thank you.

813
00:12:55,821 --> 00:12:59,825
I'm just a vagabond

814
00:12:59,825 --> 00:13:03,818
headed to Namwon
to ask a favor from a friend.

815
00:13:04,830 --> 00:13:07,833
So how is this town now?

816
00:13:07,833 --> 00:13:11,837
- The town is full of demons.
What do you mean?

817
00:13:11,837 --> 00:13:15,830
The governor is a drunken devil,
his confidant is an old zombie,

818
00:13:14,840 --> 00:13:18,833
the chiefs are gambling trolls,
and we're all grumbling ghosts.

819
00:13:23,849 --> 00:13:25,851
- This town seems to be cursed.
Do you think that's all?

820
00:13:25,851 --> 00:13:28,854
For the governor's birthday,

821
00:13:28,854 --> 00:13:32,847
each family
has to give three sacks of rice.

822
00:13:33,859 --> 00:13:37,863
He's robbing the people.

823
00:13:37,863 --> 00:13:41,856
I've heard the governor
adores a courtesan named Chunhyang,

824
00:13:43,869 --> 00:13:47,873
and enjoys her every night.
Is this true?

825
00:13:47,873 --> 00:13:54,847
What?

826
00:13:54,847 --> 00:14:04,857
You bastard!

827
00:14:04,857 --> 00:14:08,850
How dare you insult her!

828
00:14:10,863 --> 00:14:14,856
It's just what I've heard!
Why are you angry?

829
00:14:19,872 --> 00:14:22,875
Who the hell told you that?

830
00:14:22,875 --> 00:14:25,878
I'll rip his eyes out!

831
00:14:25,878 --> 00:14:29,882
And tear his ears off!

832
00:14:29,882 --> 00:14:31,884
Catch him! Get him!

833
00:14:31,884 --> 00:14:35,877
How much farther?
How far to Seoul?

834
00:14:33,886 --> 00:14:37,879
Where do I sleep today?

835
00:14:36,889 --> 00:14:40,882
Where do I sleep tomorrow?

836
00:14:40,893 --> 00:14:44,886
My fate is unlucky,
so I have to go.

837
00:14:45,898 --> 00:14:49,891
But Chunhyang's fate is worse.

838
00:14:49,902 --> 00:14:53,895
How much farther, how far?

839
00:14:59,912 --> 00:15:04,917
Hey you, come here.

840
00:15:04,917 --> 00:15:09,922
- Come here.
-Why do you call me?

841
00:15:09,922 --> 00:15:11,924
I'm a busy person, you know.

842
00:15:11,924 --> 00:15:15,928
- Because I'm from Seoul.
- From Seoul?

843
00:15:15,928 --> 00:15:19,932
Who are you visiting
at such a far place?

844
00:15:19,932 --> 00:15:23,925
I'm delivering Chunhyang Sung's
letter to Mongryong Lee.

845
00:15:23,936 --> 00:15:27,940
- Let me see the letter.
- Are you serious?

846
00:15:27,940 --> 00:15:32,945
Reading a man's letter is forbidden,

847
00:15:32,945 --> 00:15:35,948
but you ask to see
a woman's letter in public?

848
00:15:35,948 --> 00:15:39,941
You don't recognize me?

849
00:15:38,951 --> 00:15:42,944
Look carefully.

850
00:15:44,957 --> 00:15:48,950
I can't believe this!
Oh, Master Lee!

851
00:15:52,965 --> 00:15:56,958
It's a blessing to see you.

852
00:15:56,969 --> 00:16:00,973
Are you and the family well?

853
00:16:00,973 --> 00:16:05,978
Why are you dressed like this?

854
00:16:05,978 --> 00:16:08,981
Pangja, give me the letter.

855
00:16:08,981 --> 00:16:12,974
"To Mongryong Lee of Seoul"

856
00:16:11,984 --> 00:16:15,988
After you left,

857
00:16:15,988 --> 00:16:17,990
three years have past

858
00:16:17,990 --> 00:16:19,992
and I've yet to hear from you.

859
00:16:19,992 --> 00:16:23,985
Are you too intoxicated by
Seoul's beautiful spring petals?

860
00:16:23,996 --> 00:16:27,989
Or is your mind taken away
by pretty brothel women?

861
00:16:28,000 --> 00:16:32,004
Or are you going to marry
some noble lady in Seoul?

862
00:16:32,004 --> 00:16:34,006
I'm living with
these worries day and night.

863
00:16:34,006 --> 00:16:37,999
After the new governor arrived,
he asked me to court him,

864
00:16:41,013 --> 00:16:44,016
but I defied him
and he beat me severely.

865
00:16:44,016 --> 00:16:48,020
I will die soon

866
00:16:48,020 --> 00:16:54,026
at the governor's birthday feast

867
00:16:54,026 --> 00:16:58,019
when he beats me on the death chair.

868
00:16:57,029 --> 00:17:02,034
Vicious bastard!

869
00:17:02,034 --> 00:17:06,027
When I get hold of him...!

870
00:17:04,036 --> 00:17:09,041
Why do I feel such a fierce wind?

871
00:17:09,041 --> 00:17:14,046
Could it be a fierce wind
to save poor Chunhyang?

872
00:17:14,046 --> 00:17:18,039
My master can't really
be a beggar, so could he be...

873
00:17:19,051 --> 00:17:23,044
- ...an...an emissary?
- Pangja! Don't be foolish!

874
00:17:21,053 --> 00:17:41,073
Well, it's good we met.

875
00:17:41,073 --> 00:17:45,066
I want you to deliver a letter
to my home in Seoul.

876
00:17:43,075 --> 00:17:47,068
When the sun is about to set,

877
00:17:47,079 --> 00:17:51,072
he arrives in front of Chunhyang's home.

878
00:17:50,082 --> 00:17:54,075
In the back of the garden,
is a silent cry.

879
00:17:53,085 --> 00:17:57,078
He's drawn to the sound

880
00:17:54,086 --> 00:17:58,079
to take a closer look.

881
00:17:56,088 --> 00:18:00,081
He sees Chunhyang's mother

882
00:17:59,091 --> 00:18:03,084
at a small altar in the backyard.

883
00:18:02,094 --> 00:18:06,087
To the Great Dipper,

884
00:18:18,110 --> 00:18:22,103
with lit candles

885
00:18:24,116 --> 00:18:28,109
and a bowl of clean water

886
00:18:30,122 --> 00:18:34,115
set in front of her, she prays...

887
00:18:40,132 --> 00:18:44,125
I pray...I pray...

888
00:19:12,164 --> 00:19:16,157
...to the gods of heaven and earth,

889
00:19:14,166 --> 00:19:18,159
and the gods of the sun,
moon, and stars...

890
00:19:18,170 --> 00:19:22,163
Please come and help me.

891
00:19:19,171 --> 00:19:23,164
Please make my son-in-law

892
00:19:23,175 --> 00:19:26,178
a royal emissary

893
00:19:26,178 --> 00:19:30,171
or a lord of Cholla Province.

894
00:19:29,181 --> 00:19:33,174
Either one will be fine.

895
00:19:34,186 --> 00:19:38,179
Please let him
save my daughter's life.

896
00:19:39,191 --> 00:19:43,195
I passed the test...

897
00:19:43,195 --> 00:19:47,188
But I owe it mostly to their prayers.

898
00:19:44,196 --> 00:19:48,200
Is anyone home?

899
00:19:48,200 --> 00:19:52,204
Come out!

900
00:19:52,204 --> 00:19:56,197
Come out!

901
00:19:57,209 --> 00:20:01,213
May I help you?

902
00:20:01,213 --> 00:20:05,206
Go and tell your madam to come out.

903
00:20:02,214 --> 00:20:03,215
Who is it?

904
00:20:03,215 --> 00:20:07,219
Someone is asking for you madam.

905
00:20:07,219 --> 00:20:11,223
He looks like a beggar asking for food.

906
00:20:11,223 --> 00:20:15,227
What?

907
00:20:15,227 --> 00:20:18,230
Are you deaf?

908
00:20:18,230 --> 00:20:21,233
Haven't you heard?

909
00:20:21,233 --> 00:20:25,226
My daughter is in jail and about to die,

910
00:20:23,235 --> 00:20:31,243
and you ask us for food?

911
00:20:31,243 --> 00:20:35,247
We have none! Get out of here!

912
00:20:35,247 --> 00:20:42,254
I've arrived!

913
00:20:42,254 --> 00:20:46,258
It's Mongryong Lee from Seoul!

914
00:20:46,258 --> 00:20:53,265
How can this be?

915
00:20:53,265 --> 00:21:00,272
Is this true, or is it a joke?

916
00:21:00,272 --> 00:21:03,275
Hyangdan. Bring the lantern.

917
00:21:03,275 --> 00:21:06,278
Is my son-in-law really here?

918
00:21:06,278 --> 00:21:10,271
What took you so long?

919
00:21:09,281 --> 00:21:13,274
Let me see my son-in-law.

920
00:21:12,284 --> 00:21:16,277
This can't be...

921
00:21:16,288 --> 00:21:20,281
The son of the ex-governor.

922
00:21:23,295 --> 00:21:27,288
Look at the way he's dressed!

923
00:21:27,299 --> 00:21:29,301
Chunhyang's dead...

924
00:21:29,301 --> 00:21:33,305
She's dead for certain.

925
00:21:33,305 --> 00:21:37,309
I prayed day and
night you'd return as a high official,

926
00:21:37,309 --> 00:21:42,314
but you come back
as this country's filthiest beggar!

927
00:21:42,314 --> 00:21:46,307
A crisis struck our family,
so I couldn't take the exam.

928
00:21:47,319 --> 00:21:53,325
Our wealth is all gone, and
I've been begging since then.

929
00:21:53,325 --> 00:21:57,318
To remember old times,
I came back to Namwon.

930
00:21:55,327 --> 00:21:58,330
That was delicious!

931
00:21:58,330 --> 00:22:01,333
Must be your job to stuff your face.

932
00:22:01,333 --> 00:22:10,342
Your appetite reflects your living.

933
00:22:10,342 --> 00:22:13,345
I was so hungry
before I could barely think.

934
00:22:13,345 --> 00:22:17,338
But since I'm full now,
Chunhyang comes to mind.

935
00:22:16,348 --> 00:22:20,352
- Bring me to Chunhyang.
- Chunhyang's dead!

936
00:22:20,352 --> 00:22:25,357
Let's go.

937
00:22:25,357 --> 00:22:30,362
She's dying because
of me so can't I see her? Let's go.

938
00:22:30,362 --> 00:22:34,366
You can't go now.

939
00:22:34,366 --> 00:22:38,359
The governor is so strict
no man can bring food to her.

940
00:22:38,370 --> 00:22:44,376
Even a male dog can't go there.

941
00:22:44,376 --> 00:22:47,379
If they catch you,
you'll be killed.

942
00:22:47,379 --> 00:22:51,372
When the last bell strikes,
you can see her then.

943
00:22:49,381 --> 00:22:53,374
Oh, my poor baby...

944
00:22:53,385 --> 00:22:57,378
The first bell, the second,

945
00:22:58,390 --> 00:23:02,383
the third, fourth,
and fifth bell strikes.

946
00:23:00,392 --> 00:23:04,385
The time has come.

947
00:23:10,402 --> 00:23:14,395
Hyangdan leads the way.

948
00:23:13,405 --> 00:23:17,398
and the beggar son-in-law follows them

949
00:23:17,409 --> 00:23:21,402
to Chunhyang's decrepit cell.

950
00:23:21,413 --> 00:23:25,406
The night is dark and gloomy,

951
00:23:26,418 --> 00:23:30,411
not a person in sight,

952
00:23:28,420 --> 00:23:32,413
the echoes of a warbling bird...

953
00:23:33,425 --> 00:23:37,418
running water...

954
00:23:41,433 --> 00:23:45,426
wailing ghosts...

955
00:23:48,440 --> 00:23:52,433
the wind blows...

956
00:24:03,455 --> 00:24:07,448
...like trembling ground.

957
00:24:19,471 --> 00:24:23,464
Heavy rain is falling...

958
00:24:36,488 --> 00:24:40,481
Ghosts in twos and threes

959
00:24:44,496 --> 00:24:48,489
come together and cry...

960
00:24:52,504 --> 00:25:00,512
Guard.

961
00:25:00,512 --> 00:25:09,521
Guard.

962
00:25:09,521 --> 00:25:13,514
Damn guards are busy gambling again.

963
00:25:17,529 --> 00:25:26,538
...Nine.

964
00:25:26,538 --> 00:25:34,513
- Three pairs.
- Damn it! It's not my day.

965
00:25:34,513 --> 00:25:43,522
Prison keeper.

966
00:25:43,522 --> 00:25:47,515
Who is it?

967
00:25:53,532 --> 00:26:01,540
It's you again.

968
00:26:01,540 --> 00:26:09,548
We can't let anyone in until the
governor's birthday tomorrow.

969
00:26:09,548 --> 00:26:12,551
Go back.

970
00:26:12,551 --> 00:26:16,544
Don't be stubborn.
Take this, okay?

971
00:26:18,557 --> 00:26:26,565
Hey Dukbae!

972
00:26:26,565 --> 00:26:30,558
Hey Dukbae!

973
00:26:35,574 --> 00:26:39,567
Open the gate idiot!

974
00:26:37,576 --> 00:26:41,569
It's some food for my baby.
Give her this later.

975
00:26:46,585 --> 00:26:48,587
Anything else inside?

976
00:26:48,587 --> 00:26:52,580
- Oh, come on...
- Go in.

977
00:26:50,589 --> 00:26:57,596
My baby...

978
00:26:57,596 --> 00:26:59,598
Chunhyang...

979
00:26:59,598 --> 00:27:03,602
Wake up. It's your mother.

980
00:27:03,602 --> 00:27:07,595
Mother,
what are you doing here this late?

981
00:27:05,604 --> 00:27:08,607
He's here...

982
00:27:08,607 --> 00:27:12,611
Who are you talking about?

983
00:27:12,611 --> 00:27:16,604
The one you've waited day and night for.

984
00:27:15,614 --> 00:27:18,617
Be it your husband or a beggar,
he's here. See for yourself.

985
00:27:18,617 --> 00:27:20,619
Is this true?

986
00:27:20,619 --> 00:27:24,612
Hyangdan, raise the lantern.

987
00:27:24,623 --> 00:27:28,616
Chunhyang, it's me.
What happened to you?

988
00:27:27,626 --> 00:27:30,629
Oh, my husband.
What took you so long?

989
00:27:30,629 --> 00:27:32,631
What happened to your face?

990
00:27:32,631 --> 00:27:36,624
He can't save you,
and you still call him your husband?

991
00:27:34,633 --> 00:27:36,635
Chunhyang.

992
00:27:36,635 --> 00:27:38,637
My husband.

993
00:27:38,637 --> 00:27:42,630
Tomorrow at the new governor's
birthday feast, I'll be executed.

994
00:27:42,641 --> 00:27:46,634
Don't let anyone touch my body.

995
00:27:44,643 --> 00:27:48,636
Take me to Seoul and bury me
in your ancestors' graveyard.

996
00:27:48,647 --> 00:27:52,640
Then prepare a simple altar for me,
and say these words...

997
00:27:56,655 --> 00:28:00,648
Chunhyang,
cherish the drink I pour for you.

998
00:28:00,659 --> 00:28:04,652
If you do this,
I can rest in peace.

999
00:28:05,664 --> 00:28:09,657
Young Lee is disheartened.

1000
00:28:12,671 --> 00:28:15,674
Don't cry.
Don't cry.

1001
00:28:15,674 --> 00:28:19,678
My love Chunhyang, don't cry.

1002
00:28:19,678 --> 00:28:23,671
When the day is bright tomorrow,

1003
00:28:23,682 --> 00:28:26,685
either the death carriage
or the fortune carriage,

1004
00:28:26,685 --> 00:28:31,690
no one knows what you'll ride.

1005
00:28:31,690 --> 00:28:35,683
Even when the sky collapses,

1006
00:28:34,693 --> 00:28:38,686
There is a hole to escape.

1007
00:29:12,731 --> 00:29:16,724
If I said don't cry,
then please don't cry.

1008
00:29:15,734 --> 00:29:18,737
On the next day,

1009
00:29:18,737 --> 00:29:22,730
the birthday feast takes place
in Kwangharu Pavilion.

1010
00:29:21,740 --> 00:29:24,743
It's a spectacular sight.

1011
00:29:24,743 --> 00:29:29,748
The red pavilion stands
tall in the blue skies.

1012
00:29:29,748 --> 00:29:33,741
Surrounded by large shades like the clouds.

1013
00:29:31,750 --> 00:29:35,743
Covered by silk curtains on all four sides.

1014
00:29:36,755 --> 00:29:40,759
Red and blue candle lanterns

1015
00:29:40,759 --> 00:29:46,765
are hung on the open road.

1016
00:29:46,765 --> 00:29:50,758
Crowded with courtesans, musicians,
performers, and passerbies.

1017
00:29:48,767 --> 00:29:52,760
Town magistrates of other counties arrive.

1018
00:29:52,771 --> 00:29:56,764
Here comes Lord of Unbong town,
the Lord of Soonchun town,

1019
00:29:57,776 --> 00:30:01,769
the old Lord of Goksung,
the handsome Lord of Soonchan,

1020
00:30:02,781 --> 00:30:11,790
the lucky Lord of Damyang,
the chic Lord of Okgwa,

1021
00:30:11,790 --> 00:30:15,783
the Lord of Nampyung,
and the lazy Lord of Kwangju.

1022
00:30:22,801 --> 00:30:31,810
When all the lords enter,
another palanquin arrives.

1023
00:30:31,810 --> 00:30:40,819
Firecrackers crackling.

1024
00:30:40,819 --> 00:30:49,828
Sun umbrellas bumping.

1025
00:30:49,828 --> 00:30:53,832
Palanquin bearers' shoulders colliding.

1026
00:30:53,832 --> 00:30:57,825
Servants searching for their masters.

1027
00:30:58,837 --> 00:31:02,830
It's out of control.

1028
00:31:07,846 --> 00:31:11,839
Take this, take this,
take this drink,

1029
00:31:13,852 --> 00:31:17,845
and live one thousand,

1030
00:31:18,857 --> 00:31:22,850
ten thousand years.

1031
00:31:23,862 --> 00:31:27,855
Thank you for sparing your
busy time to come today.

1032
00:31:31,870 --> 00:31:35,863
...Chunshim can still twirl well even
with twins in her belly.

1033
00:31:39,878 --> 00:31:43,871
I heard the officials of Kumsan
were caught for embezzlement.

1034
00:31:47,886 --> 00:31:54,893
It was well taken care of.

1035
00:31:54,893 --> 00:31:58,886
Forget it and have a drink.

1036
00:32:23,922 --> 00:32:25,924
Look here, Soonchun.

1037
00:32:25,924 --> 00:32:28,927
Seems like this feast will go on all night.

1038
00:32:28,927 --> 00:32:34,933
- Are you staying till the end?
- Of course.

1039
00:32:34,933 --> 00:32:36,935
After the feast, Chunhyang will be flogged
to death.

1040
00:32:36,935 --> 00:32:40,928
I won't miss it for anything.

1041
00:32:37,936 --> 00:32:41,929
Our henchman can kill a person with one blow.

1042
00:32:39,938 --> 00:32:43,942
I'm sure there's someone here like that, too.

1043
00:32:43,942 --> 00:32:46,945
Why do you think there
are so many people outside?

1044
00:32:46,945 --> 00:32:49,948
There are so many people!

1045
00:32:49,948 --> 00:32:53,941
Looks like all the beggars around Namwon.

1046
00:32:50,949 --> 00:32:54,942
Two cows, fifteen pigs
and all the chickens in Namwon.

1047
00:32:57,956 --> 00:33:01,949
There's got to be something for us too.

1048
00:33:00,959 --> 00:33:04,963
Halt! You can't go in!

1049
00:33:04,963 --> 00:33:13,972
Step aside.

1050
00:33:13,972 --> 00:33:23,982
I said you can't enter!

1051
00:33:23,982 --> 00:33:27,975
Get out of my way!
I'm a nobleman too!

1052
00:33:24,983 --> 00:33:37,996
Step down!

1053
00:33:37,996 --> 00:33:42,000
Move away!
Can't you recognize a noble?

1054
00:33:42,000 --> 00:33:43,001
Step down!

1055
00:33:43,001 --> 00:33:47,005
You're tearing a poor noble's clothes!

1056
00:33:47,005 --> 00:33:53,011
What's all this noise?
- Let go of me!

1057
00:33:53,011 --> 00:33:57,004
What's all this noise?

1058
00:33:55,013 --> 00:33:59,006
A noble who looks like
a beggar insists we let him in.

1059
00:33:57,015 --> 00:34:01,019
- Governor Byun.
- Yes.

1060
00:34:01,019 --> 00:34:05,012
Although they're outworn,
he wears the clothes of a noble.

1061
00:34:05,023 --> 00:34:09,016
Just seat him in the corner,
and send him away after a drink.

1062
00:34:08,026 --> 00:34:13,031
If you desire Lord of Unbong.

1063
00:34:13,031 --> 00:34:18,036
Let him in.

1064
00:34:18,036 --> 00:34:22,040
You may enter.

1065
00:34:22,040 --> 00:34:26,033
Take your shoes off first!

1066
00:34:25,043 --> 00:34:31,049
Look here.

1067
00:34:31,049 --> 00:34:35,042
I look at your table and mine,
and it makes me angry.

1068
00:34:34,052 --> 00:34:38,045
Since you're late, it seems
your table was hastily made.

1069
00:34:36,054 --> 00:34:41,059
You may take
anything you'd like from mine.

1070
00:34:41,059 --> 00:34:45,063
Here, have a drink.

1071
00:34:45,063 --> 00:34:49,067
Lord of Unbong.

1072
00:34:49,067 --> 00:34:57,075
Yes.

1073
00:34:57,075 --> 00:35:02,080
There will be a big
meeting in Goksung this winter.

1074
00:35:02,080 --> 00:35:08,086
Please come.

1075
00:35:08,086 --> 00:35:15,093
Of course.

1076
00:35:15,093 --> 00:35:19,097
Look here.

1077
00:35:19,097 --> 00:35:23,101
You say you're Lord of Unbong town.

1078
00:35:23,101 --> 00:35:30,108
Yes I am.

1079
00:35:30,108 --> 00:35:34,101
Then call
a courtesan to sing for me also.

1080
00:35:34,112 --> 00:35:38,116
Sing for this guest.

1081
00:35:38,116 --> 00:35:42,109
He demands a singing courtesan too!

1082
00:35:46,124 --> 00:35:50,117
If you drink this wine,

1083
00:36:01,139 --> 00:36:05,132
for thousands of years

1084
00:36:10,148 --> 00:36:14,141
you will beg.

1085
00:36:13,151 --> 00:36:17,144
Since I cannot beg
for thousands of years alone,

1086
00:36:18,156 --> 00:36:22,149
why don't we all have
a drink and divide these years.

1087
00:36:20,158 --> 00:36:24,162
What a rude remark.

1088
00:36:24,162 --> 00:36:29,167
For your hospitality,

1089
00:36:29,167 --> 00:36:33,160
I'd like to improvise
a poem in honor of the new governor.

1090
00:36:33,171 --> 00:36:36,174
Governor.
Since this boy has no manners,

1091
00:36:36,174 --> 00:36:40,178
his writing will be poor.

1092
00:36:40,178 --> 00:36:44,171
Just send him away after he writes it.

1093
00:36:48,186 --> 00:36:53,191
Two words.

1094
00:36:53,191 --> 00:36:57,184
If you can't write a poem
with them, you will be clubbed.

1095
00:36:57,195 --> 00:37:01,199
Good.

1096
00:37:01,199 --> 00:37:05,192
Then give it to me.

1097
00:37:05,169 --> 00:37:09,162
Lives and feast.

1098
00:37:10,174 --> 00:37:14,167
Sure, he must know
they go in the second and last line.

1099
00:37:14,178 --> 00:37:18,171
It's not very good
so please correct it if it's wrong.

1100
00:37:17,181 --> 00:37:20,184
I apologize for my disturbance.

1101
00:37:20,184 --> 00:37:24,177
How tasteless...

1102
00:37:24,188 --> 00:37:28,181
"This wine in golden vases is
the blood of a thousand people.

1103
00:37:28,192 --> 00:37:32,185
The food on these jade tables
is the flesh of ten thousand lives.

1104
00:37:40,204 --> 00:37:44,197
When the candle wax drops,
tears of starving peasants fall.

1105
00:37:46,210 --> 00:37:50,203
And the people's complaints get louder
to pair this noisy feast."

1106
00:37:52,216 --> 00:37:56,209
This poem is laced with poison!

1107
00:38:01,225 --> 00:38:34,258
This is foolish.

1108
00:38:34,258 --> 00:38:42,266
Something has come up.
I must be going.

1109
00:38:42,266 --> 00:38:47,271
- I have to leave also.
-Why are you leaving?

1110
00:38:47,271 --> 00:38:51,264
My wife is very ill today.
I have to care for her quickly.

1111
00:38:50,274 --> 00:38:56,280
I have some urgent matters too.

1112
00:38:56,280 --> 00:39:00,273
Why are all of you worried
over some beggar's poem?

1113
00:38:58,282 --> 00:39:02,275
Please sit down.

1114
00:39:02,286 --> 00:39:06,290
Look at Mongryong,

1115
00:39:06,290 --> 00:39:10,283
He worries everyone might run away.

1116
00:39:09,293 --> 00:39:14,298
He runs out to the terrace,
and flicks open his fan.

1117
00:39:14,298 --> 00:39:21,305
Hidden in the crowd,

1118
00:39:21,305 --> 00:39:25,298
the envoy sees the signal
and storms out of the crowd,

1119
00:39:25,309 --> 00:39:28,312
They brandish their clubs,

1120
00:39:28,312 --> 00:39:30,314
raise the royal medallion like the sun,

1121
00:39:30,314 --> 00:39:34,307
thrust into the gates and shout...

1122
00:39:37,321 --> 00:39:41,314
In the King's name,
you're all under arrest!

1123
00:39:42,326 --> 00:39:46,319
You're all under arrest!

1124
00:40:08,352 --> 00:40:12,345
In the King's name,
you're all under arrest!

1125
00:40:10,354 --> 00:40:14,347
As if the heaven
collapses and the earth trembles,

1126
00:40:12,356 --> 00:40:16,349
hundreds of spectators
scatter like gushing streams.

1127
00:40:14,358 --> 00:40:18,362
What can be more frightening

1128
00:40:18,362 --> 00:40:20,364
then the thunderous roar
of the royal envoy?

1129
00:40:20,364 --> 00:40:22,366
Who can bear this whirling wind?

1130
00:40:22,366 --> 00:40:23,367
When the governor's
guests are panicking all over,

1131
00:40:23,367 --> 00:40:25,369
look at their servants'
ridiculous movements.

1132
00:40:25,369 --> 00:40:28,372
Food is stomped on,
and vases are broken,

1133
00:40:28,372 --> 00:40:33,377
Drums are split into two,
gongs roll off the pavilion

1134
00:40:33,377 --> 00:40:38,382
to make their own sound.

1135
00:40:38,382 --> 00:40:40,384
Harp strings are crushed.

1136
00:40:40,384 --> 00:40:45,389
Courtesans pin chopsticks in their hair.

1137
00:40:45,389 --> 00:40:49,382
Musicians lose their horns,
and blow from their hands.

1138
00:40:49,393 --> 00:40:53,397
Soldiers lose their guns,
and shoot from their mouths.

1139
00:40:53,397 --> 00:40:55,399
Some bump their heads,
and bleed from their nose.

1140
00:40:55,399 --> 00:40:59,392
Some fall on their face and cry,

1141
00:40:57,401 --> 00:41:22,426
passers by also run and shouts...

1142
00:41:22,426 --> 00:41:26,419
Oh no!
Our town is in trouble!

1143
00:41:25,429 --> 00:41:29,422
Namwon has the richest rice supply.

1144
00:41:30,434 --> 00:41:34,427
But you stole from it,
impoverishing the people.

1145
00:41:34,438 --> 00:41:38,431
You're supposed to keep
a close watch on the governor,

1146
00:41:38,442 --> 00:41:42,435
but you fattened
your pockets while lying to him.

1147
00:41:41,445 --> 00:41:45,438
You ignored the sick and
desperate peasants who live in misery.

1148
00:41:43,447 --> 00:41:45,449
Divide what they stole from
the poor and gave it back to them.

1149
00:41:45,449 --> 00:41:48,452
Release all the innocent people in jail.

1150
00:41:48,452 --> 00:41:52,445
And bring Chunhyang to me!

1151
00:41:50,454 --> 00:41:53,457
Chunhyang, we're here!

1152
00:41:53,457 --> 00:41:55,459
All of Namwon's
widows will stand by your side!

1153
00:41:55,459 --> 00:41:59,452
So don't worry!

1154
00:41:56,460 --> 00:42:02,466
Untie her!

1155
00:42:02,466 --> 00:42:06,459
Yes, sir!

1156
00:42:06,470 --> 00:42:14,478
Chunhyang, hear me out!

1157
00:42:14,478 --> 00:42:18,471
As a courtesan's daughter,
you disobeyed the governor!

1158
00:42:27,491 --> 00:42:31,484
How do you expect to live?

1159
00:42:31,495 --> 00:42:35,488
Serving two husbands
is the same as serving two kings.

1160
00:42:53,517 --> 00:43:00,524
So what injustice have I done?

1161
00:43:00,524 --> 00:43:04,517
Since you refused the
governor, will you refuse me also?

1162
00:43:06,530 --> 00:43:10,523
I thought the king
sent you to help the people,

1163
00:43:08,532 --> 00:43:10,534
but you're just like the
governor and other officials!

1164
00:43:10,534 --> 00:43:14,527
Stop humiliating me,
and just kill me!

1165
00:43:16,540 --> 00:43:20,533
Give this to Chunhyang,
and tell her look up at me.

1166
00:43:19,543 --> 00:43:23,536
He said to take this,
and look at him.

1167
00:43:22,546 --> 00:43:27,551
Don't just stand there!

1168
00:43:27,551 --> 00:43:31,544
Bring her to the main chamber!

1169
00:43:28,552 --> 00:43:34,558
Move away!

1170
00:43:34,558 --> 00:43:36,560
Chunhyang!

1171
00:43:36,560 --> 00:43:40,553
Chunhyang, wake up.

1172
00:43:44,568 --> 00:43:49,573
Why did you do it?

1173
00:43:49,573 --> 00:43:53,566
If you had told me,
I would've slept peacefully.

1174
00:44:16,600 --> 00:44:20,593
But I stayed up
all night worried about dying!

1175
00:44:21,605 --> 00:44:25,598
Chunhyang.

1176
00:44:24,608 --> 00:44:29,613
Don't cry.

1177
00:44:29,613 --> 00:44:33,617
The King forbade me
to give away my secret.

1178
00:44:33,617 --> 00:44:37,621
Don't cry.

1179
00:44:37,621 --> 00:44:42,626
Are the gates still closed off to me?

1180
00:44:42,626 --> 00:44:47,631
This belly bore Chunhyang!

1181
00:44:47,631 --> 00:44:51,624
I'm the mother-in-law
of the emissary!

1182
00:45:01,645 --> 00:45:03,647
People of Namwon,

1183
00:45:03,647 --> 00:45:07,651
listen to what I have to say.

1184
00:45:07,651 --> 00:45:10,654
Don't try to bear a son.

1185
00:45:10,654 --> 00:45:15,659
Bear a daughter like Chunhyang.

1186
00:45:15,659 --> 00:45:18,662
Raise her with tender and utmost care.

1187
00:45:18,662 --> 00:45:26,670
When a man from Seoul comes,

1188
00:45:26,670 --> 00:45:30,663
take him in as your son-in-law!

1189
00:45:33,677 --> 00:45:34,678
Oh...she's my daughter!

1190
00:45:34,678 --> 00:45:39,683
Oh...he's my son-in-law!

1191
00:45:39,683 --> 00:45:43,687
When you came last night,

1192
00:45:43,687 --> 00:45:46,690
I already knew everything.

1193
00:45:46,690 --> 00:45:55,699
So that your secret

1194
00:45:55,699 --> 00:45:57,701
doesn't get revealed,

1195
00:45:57,701 --> 00:46:00,704
I acted like that on purpose.

1196
00:46:00,704 --> 00:46:07,711
You were mad, weren't you?

1197
00:46:07,711 --> 00:46:14,718
Don't hate Governor Byun.

1198
00:46:14,718 --> 00:46:18,722
Without him,

1199
00:46:18,722 --> 00:46:22,715
how could my daughter
be a loyal wife?

1200
00:46:25,729 --> 00:46:30,734
You'll be sent to
Cholla province prison.

1201
00:46:30,734 --> 00:46:34,727
If you have any
objections, then do it there.

1202
00:46:35,739 --> 00:46:38,742
Adoring a pretty woman is natural.

1203
00:46:38,742 --> 00:46:42,735
But don't you think what you
did to Chunhyang was too harsh?

1204
00:46:42,746 --> 00:46:45,749
Class has a definite order.

1205
00:46:45,749 --> 00:46:48,752
A daughter of
a courtesan becomes one naturally.

1206
00:46:48,752 --> 00:46:51,755
She didn't disobey just me,

1207
00:46:51,755 --> 00:46:55,748
but she disgraced
the law, and committed treason.

1208
00:46:54,758 --> 00:46:58,751
It wasn't injustice...

1209
00:46:57,761 --> 00:46:59,763
it was her will to be a human being.

1210
00:46:59,763 --> 00:47:00,764
Later...Mongryong

1211
00:47:00,764 --> 00:47:01,765
goes from town to town,

1212
00:47:01,765 --> 00:47:09,773
and finishes his investigation.

1213
00:47:09,773 --> 00:47:13,766
He returns to Seoul,

1214
00:47:13,777 --> 00:47:16,780
and reports what he had seen.

1215
00:47:16,780 --> 00:47:21,785
The King compliments him...

1216
00:47:21,785 --> 00:47:25,778
You saved the country
from great worry.

1217
00:47:24,788 --> 00:47:41,805
You're a national hero.

1218
00:47:41,805 --> 00:47:46,810
Another official tells the King

1219
00:47:46,810 --> 00:47:50,803
about loyal Chunhyang of Namwon

1220
00:47:50,814 --> 00:47:55,819
and the King bestows on her

1221
00:47:55,819 --> 00:48:00,824
an honorable award for loyalty.

1222
00:48:00,824 --> 00:48:05,829
As for the people of Namwon,

1223
00:48:05,829 --> 00:48:08,832
the King lifts the taxes.

1224
00:48:08,832 --> 00:48:12,825
They all live in peace,

1225
00:48:12,836 --> 00:48:16,829
but who knows
what will happen after this story.

